Twice the Hype has been entered in the 10th Annual Independent Music Awards for their single “Twice the Hype” under hip hop single category.

“Ralph (Kid Cool) & Rob (T-Hype) Twin Brothers called Twice the Hype busted into the Rap/ Hip-Hop scene in the late 90’s. They performed all over the DC metro area clubs for several years and was featured on DC’s local radio station WPGC 95.5 Home Jams and Billboard’s Magazine for DC’s best new up and coming hip-hop artist.”

Unique dynamic duo Ralph (Kid Cool ) & Robert (T-Hype) known as Twice the hype raps in a urban style hip hop form representing Washington, DC artists while giving you a Miami sound club mix with a New York hip hop edge.

Members of ASCAP & SoundExchange
